File: According to officials, this year alone between 13 and 15 children have been recovered after heavy flooding in the area. KWAZULU-NATAL - The body of Siyabonga Ndlovu (9), who drowned in the uMvoti River in KwaZulu-Natal, has been found. He went missing five days ago. It's believed he'd gone swimming in the river. IPSS's Medical Rescue has confirmed that it, along with the police's diving unit and the K9 unit from Umhlali, had recovered the body. According to officials, this year alone between 13 and 15 children have been recovered after heavy flooding in the area.